# Netlify security headers. Vite copies /public/_headers -> /dist/_headers at build.
#
# ONE policy applied to /* (every route). This is deliberate: the app is an SPA, so Netlify
# rewrites every unmatched path to the same index.html. A per-route CSP would be bypassable by
# just loading the app via an unlisted path (same bundle, no header) — so the CSP MUST cover /*.
#
# The single policy is therefore the UNION of what the whole app loads:
#   - self + inline (index.html has inline theme/font-preload scripts + inline styles)
#   - Cloudflare Turnstile      (public quote form anti-spam)
#   - Google Fonts              (fonts.googleapis.com / fonts.gstatic.com)
#   - Supabase                  (REST + realtime wss + storage images + PDF preview iframe)
#   - Plaid Link                (cdn.plaid.com script; *.plaid.com frames/connect) — accounting
#   - Office / Google Docs      (view.officeapps.live.com, docs.google.com) — attachment viewers
#   - api.trello.com            (Trello import)
#
# 'unsafe-inline' is required by the inline scripts/styles above; the policy still blocks loading
# scripts / connecting / framing to any origin not listed here. Tightening script-src to
# nonces/hashes is a follow-up. 'wasm-unsafe-eval' is required by the barcode scanner's ZXing
# WebAssembly fallback (src/scanner/detectors.ts) on browsers without a fully capable native
# BarcodeDetector (iOS Safari, desktop) — it permits wasm compilation only, NOT JS eval(). The
# .wasm itself is bundled and fetched same-origin (connect-src 'self'), no CDN involved. The
# service worker (/sw.js) is same-origin.
#
# SMOKE-TEST BEFORE TRUSTING IN PROD: load a deploy preview and exercise Plaid Link, the
# Office/Docs attachment viewers, PDF preview, and the barcode scanner while watching the
# console for CSP violations. Quick rollback if something trips: rename the header to
# `Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only` (reports, does not block) until the missing origin is added.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=(), microphone=(self), camera=(self)
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://cdn.plaid.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com data:; img-src 'self' data: blob: https://*.supabase.co; connect-src 'self' https://*.supabase.co wss://*.supabase.co https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://*.plaid.com https://cdn.plaid.com https://api.trello.com; frame-src 'self' blob: https://*.supabase.co https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://*.plaid.com https://cdn.plaid.com https://view.officeapps.live.com https://docs.google.com
